      <body>Nice looking patch. However, you can already do this.

@@@ ruby
class MyController &lt; ActionController::Base
  before_filter :auth, :if =&gt; Proc.new { |controller|
      controller.action_name =~ /.*_create/
    }
end
@@@

Hopefully that solves your problem.</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Nice looking patch. However, you can already do this.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;
class MyController &amp;lt; ActionController::Base
  before_filter :auth, :if =&amp;gt; Proc.new { |controller|
      controller.action_name =~ /.*_create/
    }
end
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hopefully that solves your problem.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
